        "The Real Estate Regulation Company is the central regulatory body for the real estate sector in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. Established in 2017 to oversee non-governmental real estate activities, this company plays a pivotal role in Saudi Vision 2030 by enhancing market transparency, issuing licenses, and protecting consumer rights to foster a world-class investment environment."
